DUTIES:
We are recruiting for a challenging project we have recently started with a new client. Currently we are looking for people interested in working in a HR Service Center, as SWISS Payroll Assistants

Responsibilities:
Calculating and inputting monthly/weekly payroll data into the payroll system/database in accordance with statutory and contractual obligations and to pre-defined timescales 
Compiling data for analysis and reporting;
Processing and monitoring all staffing changes including starters, secondments, transfers, leavers and other amendments to salaries and employee data in compliance with policy and payroll requirements.
Inputting, calculating and recording of sickness payments both statutory and occupational.
Inputting, calculating and recording of maternity, paternity and adoption payments both statutory and occupational.
Generating and distributing checks and pay slips;
Researching and responding to payroll questions and inquiries;
Processing, collecting and providing garnishment remittances and levies; completing and returning forms and notifying employees of changes made;
Working with third party vendors to establish deduction procedures; reviewing and auditing deduction process and results and working with vendors to correct problems/issues as needed;
Providing accurate payroll reporting.
Performs other duties/projects as assigned.

